SMALL STRAWS IN A SOFT WIND by Marsha Burns
Be quiet, child, and be aware of the spiritual environment. Do you sense
the moving of My Spirit? I tell you truly that there is much activity
and excitement in the heavenly realm in anticipation of what is about to
be done on earth. Prepare by establishing yourself in faith on the firm
foundation of My Word. Shut your eyes to whatever causes you to doubt My
power and presence. Turn a deaf ear to everything that questions My
intentions and purposes for your good, says the Lord.
Numbers 23:19 "God is not a man, that He should lie, nor a son of man,
that He should repent. Has He said, and will He not do? Or has He
spoken, and will He not make it good?

Refuse to allow your circumstances to circumvent your faith. Your faith
is your most powerful possession. Do not open the door for the enemy to
undermine your effectiveness through doubt and unbelief. Be steadfast
and immovable. Believe, and then speak. Speak out of the abundance of
your heart with undaunted faith. Speak forth the word of truth, says the
Lord.
Romans 1:17 For in it (the Gospel of Christ) the righteousness of God is
revealed from faith to faith; as it is written, "The just shall live by
faith."

Be still, beloved. Your heart has become overwhelmed with all that is
ahead of you. But, you don't have to face these things all at this time,
nor do you have to face these things alone, for I am with you to bring
you through in courage and boldness. Do not be distressed or become
disheartened; my strength is sufficient to meet the troubles of this
day. Take one day at a time, and I will lead you one step at a time. Do
not be afraid, says the Lord.
Psalm 124:2-8 "If it had not been the LORD who was on our side, when men
rose up against us, then they would have swallowed us alive, when their
wrath was kindled against us; then the waters would have overwhelmed us,
the stream would have gone over our soul; then the swollen waters would
have gone over our soul." Blessed be the LORD, Who has not given us as
prey to their teeth. Our soul has escaped as a bird from the snare of
the fowlers; the snare is broken, and we have escaped. Our help is in
the name of the LORD, Who made heaven and earth.

Be liberated! I call you to come into the realm of freedom from all
restriction and bondage. Come forth! Break loose! Now is a time when you
can make considerable progress in attaining your desires and goals.
Refuse to allow the enemy of your soul to keep you from breaking
through. Press on and push through. Be strong, says the Lord.
Ephesians 6:10 Finally, my brethren, be strong in the Lord and in the
power of His might.

